        "covid intro" => "Coronavirus, also known as Sars-Cov-2, has become a crucial part of our lives the past year. It has affected us economically, socially and has a serious impact to our health condition both physically and mentally. Unfortunately, it doesn't look like we are going to be get rid of the virus anytime soon. Some people might even say that Covid-19 is the new normal.",
        "covid outbreak" => "The virus outbreak, that initially started in China, became a worldwide concern very quickly and unexpectedly, because as it turned out, the coronavirus is life-threatening but also very contagious too, as it can be transmitted via the air. Therefore, the virus specialists warned the public and urged them to take immediate precautions and measures to prevent the illness from spreading and avoid the worst of it.",
